def: To recognize or judge in advance; to forebode. [Obs.] Udall.Laugh at your misery, as foredeeming you An idle meteor. J. Webster.
Having but one hand, or one workman; also, alone; unassisted.
Covered with very soft hairs pressed close to the surface; as,a sericeous leaf.
To conceal, as in bushes; to hide. [Obs.] Shelton.
Limestone containing a large percentage of iron carbonate, andhence turning brown on exposure.
A small herb, of the genus Myosotis (M. palustris, incespitosa,etc.), bearing a beautiful blue flower, and extensively consideredthe emblem of fidelity.
The state or quality of being imperdible. [Obs.] Derham.
A salt of selenic acid; -- formerly called also seleniate.
